      <title outputclass="H4ForH3_1_9" class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">49.109-1</ph> General.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <p otherprops="Body"
            outputclass="Body"
            class="- topic/p "
            id="d2878e13">When
a termination settlement has been negotiated and all required reviews
have been obtained, the contractor and the TCO shall execute a settlement
agreement on <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="https://www.gsa.gov/forms-library/amendment-solicitationmodification-contract"
                     format="html"
                     scope="external"
                     class="- topic/xref ">Standard Form 30</xref>
            </ph> (Amendment
of Solicitation/Modification of Contract) (see <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="FAR-i1067386.dita#i1067386"
                     base="i1067386"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">49.603</xref>
            </ph>). The
settlement shall cover-</p>
         <ol id="d2864e28" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2878e32" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  Any setoffs that the Government
has against the contractor that may be applied against the terminated
contract and</p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2878e41" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  All settlement proposals of subcontractors,
except proposals that are specifically excepted from the agreement
and reserved for separate settlement.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
